                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" fkcefr="c2" id="alkali_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a chemical substance that reacts with <span class="ndv" xt="ndv" tofix="" href="acid_topg_1">acids</span> to form a salt and gives a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/solution" title="solution definition"><span class="ndv">solution</span></a> with a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/ph" title="pH definition"><span class="ndv">pH</span></a> of more than seven when it is <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/dissolve#dissolve_topg_1" title="dissolved definition"><span class="ndv">dissolved</span></a> <span class="gloss" htag="span" hclass="gloss">(= mixed with a liquid and becoming part of it)</span> in water</span></span> <span class="xrefs" hclass="xrefs" xt="cp" htag="span"><span class="prefix">compare</span> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/acid_1" title="acid definition"><span class="xr-g" bord="n" dict="all" href="acid_subentryg_1:acid_topg_2"><span class="xh">acid</span></span></a></span><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/physics-and-chemistry?level=c2" title="Topic physics-and-chemistry"><span class="topic" href="l2:science_and_technology:physics_and_chemistry?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Physics and chemistry</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="alkali_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late Middle English (denoting a saline substance derived from the ashes of various plants, including glasswort, a salt-marsh plant formerly used to make glass): from medieval Latin, from Arabic <span class="ei">al-qalī</span> ‘calcined ashes (of the glasswort etc.), reduced through exposure to strong heat’, from <span class="ei">qalā</span> ‘fry, roast’.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
